# Create a new Rust project
cargo new atlas-search-partial-match-tutorial && cd atlas-search-partial-match-tutorial

Add the following dependencies to your ``Cargo.toml`` file:
``````
[dependencies]
serde = "1.0"
futures = "0.3"
tokio = {version = "1.0", features = ["full"]}

[dependencies.mongodb]
version = "3.0"
```For detailed installation instructions, see the
[MongoDB Rust Driver Download and Install](rust/quick-start/download-and-install) guide.Paste the following code into `src/main.rs` based on the operator
you intend to use for your partial match queries.autocomplete```rust
use mongodb::bson::{doc, Document};
use mongodb::{Client, Collection, SearchIndexModel, SearchIndexType};

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() -> mongodb::error::Result<()> {
    // Connects to your Atlas deployment
    let uri = "<connection-string>";

    let client = Client::with_uri_str(uri).await?;

    // Sets the namespace
    let collection: Collection<Document> = client
        .database("sample_mflix")
        .collection("movies");

    // Defines your MongoDB Search index for autocomplete
    let index = doc! {
        "mappings": doc! {
            "dynamic": false,
            "fields": doc! {
                "plot": doc! {
                    "type": "autocomplete",
                    "tokenization": "edgeGram",
                    "minGrams": 2,
                    "maxGrams": 15,
                    "foldDiacritics": true
                }
            }
        }
    };

    let idx_model = SearchIndexModel::builder()
        .definition(index)
        .name("partial-match-tutorial".to_string())
        .index_type(SearchIndexType::Search)
        .build();

    // Runs the helper method
    let result = collection.create_search_index(idx_model).await?;
    println!("{}", result);

    Ok(())
}

```The index definition specifies the following:* Uses [dynamic mappings](static-dynamic-mappings) with
  `dynamic: false` to only index specified fields

* Indexes the `plot` field as [autocomplete](autocomplete-ref)
  type to enable search-as-you-type functionality

* Configures `edgeGram` tokenization with 2-15 character grams

* Enables diacritic folding for broader matchingphrase```rust
